The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 80-yr-old run over by bus
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      80-yr-old run over by bus
          A STAFF REPORTER                               
	An 80-year-old woman died after being run over by a chartered bus at the crossing of WC Bonerjee Road and CR Avenue near Girish Park on Friday morning.        
	Mayarani Dutta was crossing CR Avenue on the way to her Balaram De Street home when the bus hit her. Police said the signal was green for the bus.        
	Mayarani was returning from the market around 10.15am when the mishap occurred. I saw people running towards the main road, where she lay in a pool of blood, said the womans neighbour Jharna Singha Roy.         
	Mayarani died after she was taken to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital.         
	A mob broke the windows of the bus. Officers from Girish Park police station controlled the crowd.        
	Traffic on both flanks of the road was affected for half an hour.        
	Residents blamed lax policing at the crossing for the mishap. The bus driver was at large till late on Friday.                                                                                                                                                          
